  "prompt": "Are there any websites like DAAD for masters in US?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several websites and organizations that provide information and resources for international students seeking to pursue a master's degree in the United States. Here are some notable ones:\n\n1. **EducationUSA**: This is a U.S. Department of State network that offers information on studying in the U.S., including resources for finding colleges, applying, and understanding the student visa process.\n\n   Website: [educationusa.state.gov](https://educationusa.state.gov)\n\n2. **Institute of International Education (IIE)**: This organization provides resources and research on global education, including scholarships and grant opportunities for international students.\n\n   Website: [iie.org](https://www.iie.org)\n\n3. **GradSchools.com**: This website offers a comprehensive database of graduate programs in the U.S. and provides resources for prospective students, including application tips and information on funding.\n\n   Website: [gradschools.com](https://www.gradschools.com)\n\n4. **Peterson\u2019s**: This is a well-known educational resource that provides information about graduate programs, scholarships, and test preparation.\n\n   Website: [petersons.com](https://www.petersons.com)\n\n5. **Common Application**: Some universities in the U.S. accept the Common App for graduate programs, making it easier to apply to multiple schools with a single application. \n\n   Website: [commonapp.org](https://www.commonapp.org)\n\n6. **Scholarships.com**: This site provides a database of scholarships that can be filtered based on your criteria, including international scholarships for grad students.\n\n   Website: [scholarships.com](https://www.scholarships.com)\n\n7. **Chevening Scholarships**: While primarily focused on UK education, Chevening provides resources and connections for those interested in international study opportunities, including in the U.S.\n\n   Website: [chevening.org](https://www.chevening.org)\n\nEach of these resources can help you navigate the process of applying for master's programs in the U.S., including finding financial aid, understanding application requirements, and more.",
